01:18.675 --> 01:22.478
[ Band plays ]

01:22.480 --> 01:23.479
[ Giggling ]

01:23.481 --> 01:26.515
Go away, you devil!
Go!

01:26.517 --> 01:28.717
That little brat was
looking up your skirt.

01:28.719 --> 01:30.352
Boy: Paper here!

01:30.354 --> 01:33.389
New York City celebrates
inauguration day-y-y!

01:33.391 --> 01:35.691
Paper!
Get your paper here!

01:43.135 --> 01:44.229
[ Door opens ]

01:44.349 --> 01:46.155
Detectives, sorry
to keep you waiting.

01:46.275 --> 01:47.817
Come on in.

01:49.673 --> 01:51.357
We have a man dead

01:51.477 --> 01:53.409
in the Centre Street Tenement,

01:53.411 --> 01:57.913
an uptown man,
wealthy, visible,

01:57.915 --> 02:00.115
and wouldn't you know?
Good.

02:00.117 --> 02:02.284
Alderman Stephen Bartlett.

02:02.286 --> 02:04.286
He was earnest.

02:04.288 --> 02:07.022
He attended to the needs
of immigrants and the poor.

02:07.024 --> 02:09.091
He deserves no scandal.

02:09.092 --> 02:11.460
Investigate prudently,

02:11.462 --> 02:12.461
discreetly...

02:12.463 --> 02:14.163
All specialties
of Francis Maguire.

02:14.165 --> 02:16.309
Careful, now.
Collaboration is

02:16.429 --> 02:17.930
the best way to erase the mark

02:18.050 --> 02:20.669
Keating left on
the 6th precinct.

02:20.671 --> 02:23.639
You and Francis Maguire
are likeminded opposites...

02:23.641 --> 02:25.774
the best detective pairing.

02:27.510 --> 02:29.678
The city will be headed
to Union Square

02:29.680 --> 02:31.847
for inauguration festivities.

02:31.849 --> 02:34.917
A good distraction from
any scandalous findings.

02:40.790 --> 02:42.791
[ Clock ticks ]

02:46.763 --> 02:49.265
[ Gasp ]

02:49.267 --> 02:53.002
Sara! Ohh!

02:53.004 --> 02:55.304
[ Laughs ]

02:55.306 --> 02:57.139
Oh!

02:57.141 --> 03:00.276
Oh, my darlin'!

03:00.278 --> 03:03.078
[ Laughter ]

03:03.080 --> 03:04.179
My darlin'.

03:04.181 --> 03:07.262
Oh! Let me
get a look at you!

03:07.382 --> 03:09.451
Oh, beautiful.

03:09.453 --> 03:11.453
Sara Freeman!

03:11.455 --> 03:13.856
Look at you,

03:13.858 --> 03:17.493
you a married lady.

03:17.495 --> 03:19.395
[ Crying ]

03:19.397 --> 03:21.563
Mama, I've been afraid
to let myself

03:21.565 --> 03:24.443
consider this moment and, now,

03:24.563 --> 03:26.794
praise God!

03:32.242 --> 03:34.977
[ Laughter ]

03:34.979 --> 03:36.478
You've changed our lives.

03:36.480 --> 03:40.582
How did you convince
them to free her?

03:40.584 --> 03:43.085
There was no freeing of
Hattie Lemaster.

03:43.087 --> 03:45.721
There was a purchase.

03:45.723 --> 03:48.390
Quite a bundle of bills.

03:48.392 --> 03:50.192
My family is forever
in your debt.

03:50.194 --> 03:52.328
Matthew,

03:52.330 --> 03:54.897
forever is a terribly
limitless void.

03:54.899 --> 03:57.333
Matthew! Matthew!

04:03.273 --> 04:05.207
Sweet Matthew.

04:09.579 --> 04:12.414
Thank you for looking
after my baby girl.

04:12.416 --> 04:16.185
Look, I have another son.

04:16.187 --> 04:20.175
Yet another blessing.

04:20.475 --> 04:21.940
How about the rest of 'em?

04:21.942 --> 04:24.610
Where y'all hiding
your brothers?

04:30.484 --> 04:33.686
No, I have had a change of...

04:33.688 --> 04:34.854
Heart.

04:34.856 --> 04:37.089
I will not testify
against Kennedy.

04:37.091 --> 04:39.725
Have you gone as mad
as our defendant?

04:39.727 --> 04:41.260
After all your effort

04:41.262 --> 04:42.762
to stop that traitor
from burning New York,

04:42.764 --> 04:44.797
you, on the very day
of the trial,

04:44.799 --> 04:46.933
choose to cripple
the government's case?

04:46.935 --> 04:49.669
Once, I myself
was termed a cripple.

04:49.671 --> 04:52.104
Then, I recognized
another way to walk.

04:52.106 --> 04:55.374
Robert Cobb Kennedy
will go free.

04:55.376 --> 04:57.143
Colonel.

04:57.145 --> 05:00.780
Confederate fire will
consume this city.

05:02.749 --> 05:05.584
I hope you will blame yourself.

05:10.190 --> 05:15.094
What, exactly, happened
to my boys?

05:17.898 --> 05:21.667
The circumstance surrounding
Louis's and Thomas's deaths

05:21.669 --> 05:23.436
were terrible.

05:23.438 --> 05:25.471
When I was, uh...

05:25.473 --> 05:29.008
the draft riots and...

05:29.010 --> 05:30.209
things became...

05:30.211 --> 05:34.413
Chaotic.

05:34.415 --> 05:36.382
Louis and Thomas were called

05:36.384 --> 05:38.684
to work extra hours
on the ferry,

05:38.686 --> 05:41.760
as the Irish laborers
abandoned their jobs,

05:41.880 --> 05:44.023
abandoned normal life
in its entirety,

05:44.025 --> 05:47.560
and tore the city apart.

05:49.527 --> 05:50.825
On...

05:53.701 --> 05:57.003
July 13th,

05:57.005 --> 05:59.839
during a crossing
to Greenpoint,

05:59.841 --> 06:03.676
two ferries collided.

06:03.678 --> 06:05.778
When the engines caught fire,

06:05.780 --> 06:07.913
Louis and Thomas

06:07.915 --> 06:11.384
loaded passengers
into lifeboats

06:11.386 --> 06:15.021
to safety.

06:15.023 --> 06:17.356
A surviving crewman
told me they acted

06:17.358 --> 06:19.592
with no regard
for their own lives.

06:19.594 --> 06:22.294
[ Moan ]

06:22.296 --> 06:24.530
He called them heroes.

06:24.532 --> 06:28.501
[ Sobbing ]

06:38.078 --> 06:39.178
This it?

06:39.180 --> 06:40.446
Aye.

06:40.448 --> 06:42.279
Not where Alderman
Bartlett expected

06:42.399 --> 06:44.447
to meet his end, I'll wager.

06:53.160 --> 06:54.260
Hey.

06:54.262 --> 06:55.294
Copper.

07:00.000 --> 07:02.635
Oh, Christ, of all the...

07:02.637 --> 07:04.603
Jesus.

07:04.605 --> 07:06.472
[ Purr ]

07:06.474 --> 07:08.874
[ Hiss ]

07:08.876 --> 07:10.242
Francis, you need me

07:10.244 --> 07:11.610
to stand down
the kitty-cat?

07:11.612 --> 07:13.112
Ah, shut your...

07:13.114 --> 07:15.081
[ Purring ]

07:15.083 --> 07:17.550
[ Hiss ]

07:17.552 --> 07:19.718
[ Hiss ]

07:19.720 --> 07:21.487
I can't stand 'em!
They're witches!

07:21.489 --> 07:22.922
Don't pretend your ma
didn't warn you

07:22.924 --> 07:24.290
a hundred times.

07:24.292 --> 07:26.592
[Hiss] Hey!

07:26.594 --> 07:27.927
Out!

07:27.929 --> 07:29.395
[ Meow ]

07:34.367 --> 07:35.768
His pocket watch survived.

07:35.770 --> 07:38.270
Whoever lived here
is long gone,

07:38.272 --> 07:39.638
but someone took
the time to pack up.

07:39.640 --> 07:43.909
A woman.

07:50.330 --> 07:53.452
Strangled, but not
with a normal rope.

07:53.454 --> 07:55.904
See how thin it is?
Cut right into him.

08:01.094 --> 08:04.163
His coat's still here.

08:04.165 --> 08:06.699
Alderman Bartlett,
what were you

08:06.701 --> 08:09.802
really up to, down
here in Five Points?

08:09.804 --> 08:11.270
Corky, the only reason
you end up

08:11.272 --> 08:12.771
in that position is sex.

08:12.773 --> 08:14.273
- No, no, miss.
- To think,

08:14.275 --> 08:16.583
Teresa considered that the
best arse she could get.

08:16.703 --> 08:17.982
Teresa who?

08:18.102 --> 08:19.545
Teresa Trembley, o' course.

08:19.547 --> 08:23.313
And Teresa was from
outside the city?

08:23.433 --> 08:25.551
Came here all
by her pretty self,

08:25.553 --> 08:27.219
from Hamilton, Ontario.

08:27.221 --> 08:28.888
Who are you, again?

08:28.890 --> 08:30.456
Mab O'Dwyer.

08:30.458 --> 08:32.323
Longest tenant
in the Centre Street.

08:32.326 --> 08:34.527
Congratulations.

08:34.529 --> 08:36.128
What did you see last night?

08:36.130 --> 08:37.696
The usual dance.

08:37.698 --> 08:40.332
Then, something different...

08:40.333 --> 08:41.967
Another fella come by
and, later,

08:41.969 --> 08:43.369
there was commotion.

08:43.371 --> 08:45.829
So the bloke,
what'd he look like?

08:45.949 --> 08:48.034
Ugh, they hollered a good lot

08:48.154 --> 08:50.097
before I nearly knocked
through the wall.

08:50.603 --> 08:53.846
So, you didn't actually
see anything, then?

08:53.848 --> 08:56.766
The charges brought
against the defendant,

08:56.886 --> 08:58.489
Robert Cobb Kennedy,

08:58.609 --> 09:00.110
are as follows...

09:00.230 --> 09:04.356
(1) As a captain
in the military service

09:04.358 --> 09:07.560
of the insurgent states,
was found acting as a spy

09:07.562 --> 09:10.062
in the city of New York.

09:10.064 --> 09:13.999
(2) In violation
of the law of war,

09:14.001 --> 09:16.694
undertook irregular
and unlawful warfare

09:16.814 --> 09:17.868
in the city of New York,

09:17.988 --> 09:21.006
by setting fire thereto.

09:21.008 --> 09:23.342
How does the accused plead?

09:23.344 --> 09:26.145
Not guilty, to all charges.

09:26.147 --> 09:28.547
Are you prepared to proceed
with this trial

09:28.549 --> 09:29.815
under the judgment of
these officers?

09:29.817 --> 09:32.418
I am.

09:32.420 --> 09:34.687
And I will defend myself.

09:41.861 --> 09:43.229
Boy: Get your paper!

09:46.533 --> 09:48.033
Good morning.

09:48.035 --> 09:51.103
Good mornin'.

09:51.105 --> 09:54.673
Oh, my God, you're pregnant!

09:54.675 --> 09:56.175
You didn't know?

09:56.177 --> 09:57.610
Should I have?

09:57.612 --> 10:03.148
Hmm, the way gossip
moves in this town?

10:03.150 --> 10:04.416
Lovely news, actually,

10:04.418 --> 10:06.552
that a woman can still
have a private life.

10:06.554 --> 10:09.021
No, Eva, tell me...

10:09.023 --> 10:11.023
Should I have known?

10:11.025 --> 10:14.126
Personally, I've never
operated on shoulds.

10:18.965 --> 10:20.466
This concludes
the opening session

10:20.468 --> 10:21.967
of this tribunal hearing.

10:21.969 --> 10:24.346
We will reconvene
in one half-hour's time.

10:24.466 --> 10:25.826
[ Gavel bangs ]

10:26.440 --> 10:29.942
[ Spectators murmur ]

10:29.944 --> 10:32.778
Hey.

10:32.780 --> 10:36.376
Your neighbor Alderman Bartlett,
what do you know of his wife?

10:36.496 --> 10:38.951
Corky, you always pick the best ones,
but, as you can see,

10:39.071 --> 10:40.286
we're in the middle
of a military tribunal.

10:40.288 --> 10:42.273
Then give me what you
have, quickly.

10:44.958 --> 10:46.492
The alderman's first wife died

10:46.494 --> 10:48.927
several years ago...
cholera.

10:48.929 --> 10:50.562
Last winter,
he married Constance,

10:50.564 --> 10:52.164
a society doyenne.

10:52.166 --> 10:54.066
Sounds like good luck
after bad.

10:54.068 --> 10:56.068
Last month, Constance
went out to Paris,

10:56.070 --> 10:57.970
not scheduled to return
until spring.

10:57.972 --> 10:59.271
That'd be nice.

10:59.273 --> 11:02.074
It gets better.

11:02.076 --> 11:03.909
The alderman has a grown son

11:03.911 --> 11:05.711
by his first wife, a Benjamin.

11:05.713 --> 11:07.613
Since the wedding, there's
been uptown whisper

11:07.615 --> 11:09.114
that Benny's been
putting the wood

11:09.116 --> 11:11.583
to his stepmother, who's
younger than he is.

11:17.457 --> 11:19.558
I take it that Benjamin's
not in Paris?

11:19.560 --> 11:21.427
[ Chuckle ]

11:21.429 --> 11:23.495
When Constance flitted off,

11:23.497 --> 11:25.531
Benny moved out
to his family estate

11:25.533 --> 11:26.965
on the Bronx River.

11:26.967 --> 11:28.967
[ Whistling ]

11:33.440 --> 11:35.307
Ben fancies himself a pianist.

11:35.309 --> 11:36.542
[ Laughs ]

11:36.544 --> 11:40.412
Art demands space
and beauty, Corky.

11:40.414 --> 11:41.714
Thank you.

11:46.619 --> 11:48.787
Corcoran:
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

12:00.834 --> 12:02.601
Finally!
The carriage.

12:02.603 --> 12:03.702
Goodness,

12:03.704 --> 12:05.671
they're hiring anyone
today, aren't they?

12:05.673 --> 12:08.707
- Ya uppity little...
- Hey!

12:08.709 --> 12:10.275
We're the police.
We're from the sixth ward.

12:10.277 --> 12:11.910
The sixth?
Unfortunate.

12:11.912 --> 12:14.146
I prefer to travel
in a bit more style.

12:14.148 --> 12:16.582
Listen, we need to...

12:16.584 --> 12:18.016
Excuse me!
You're smudging

12:18.018 --> 12:20.119
my chesterfield
with downtown filth!

12:20.121 --> 12:21.954
We need to talk
about your father.

12:21.956 --> 12:23.055
Bad timing.

12:23.057 --> 12:24.790
I'm playing at an
inauguration party...

12:24.792 --> 12:26.859
For the love
of Christ, get out!

12:26.861 --> 12:28.560
Please!

12:28.562 --> 12:30.763
[ Grunting ]

12:30.765 --> 12:34.434
Help!
This is kidnapping!

12:34.554 --> 12:36.368
This man is a lunatic!

12:36.370 --> 12:38.404
Downtown filth?

12:38.406 --> 12:40.973
Sometimes it shines
like copper.

12:40.975 --> 12:42.107
Get in!

12:44.244 --> 12:46.011
There's a good lad.

12:46.013 --> 12:47.746
Lovely day.

12:47.748 --> 12:49.848
Ha!

12:57.870 --> 12:59.200
Robert.

13:01.892 --> 13:03.643
Husband.

13:06.661 --> 13:09.196
So you are returned
from the South.

13:17.439 --> 13:18.806
I wish I had been invited

13:18.808 --> 13:21.208
to the honeymoon.

13:21.210 --> 13:22.309
The Freemans...

13:22.311 --> 13:23.811
I've realized
in the last two weeks

13:23.813 --> 13:27.748
that I may not like
being in love.

13:31.052 --> 13:35.022
My actions were a mistake,

13:35.024 --> 13:36.824
borne of lies,

13:36.826 --> 13:39.660
manipulation.

13:39.662 --> 13:43.797
I am the woman you know,

13:43.799 --> 13:47.101
only now, brimming with remorse

13:47.103 --> 13:50.004
and fear.

13:50.006 --> 13:54.375
If you could just...

13:54.377 --> 13:56.443
[Crying] I have refused

13:56.445 --> 13:57.945
to testify against Kennedy.

14:05.851 --> 14:07.921
Oh, thank God.

14:23.805 --> 14:26.407
You like Five Points?

14:26.409 --> 14:27.841
Seems like a good place

14:27.843 --> 14:29.410
to do dirty work, huh?

14:29.412 --> 14:31.178
I have no idea to what you refer.

14:31.180 --> 14:33.547
I am, however,
unprofessionally,

14:33.549 --> 14:34.915
uncharacteristically,
late for...

14:34.917 --> 14:36.517
Benjamin, we know

14:36.519 --> 14:38.519
your father's recent marriage

14:38.521 --> 14:39.604
must've caused a bit of stress.

14:39.724 --> 14:41.789
I see two explanations...

14:41.791 --> 14:44.058
You were jealous pappy
got himself a ladybird,

14:44.060 --> 14:48.195
wanted her for yourself,
or, you had her first

14:48.197 --> 14:50.631
and she claimed
she couldn't choose.

14:50.633 --> 14:53.500
This is Constance,

14:53.502 --> 14:55.669
right?

14:55.671 --> 14:57.871
Tell us about your stepmother.

14:57.873 --> 14:59.473
Oh, hold the horse.

14:59.475 --> 15:03.677
Christ, I'd be ridin' her, too.

15:03.679 --> 15:06.113
You would, wouldn't
you, Francis?

15:06.115 --> 15:07.681
While the alderman was seeing

15:07.683 --> 15:08.982
to the greater needs
of the city,

15:08.984 --> 15:12.653
were you lying in his bed,
screwing his wife?

15:12.655 --> 15:14.154
No!

15:14.156 --> 15:16.156
What, in the name of
the law and our Lord,

15:16.158 --> 15:17.658
do you think you're doing?

15:17.660 --> 15:19.593
This arrest is complete...

15:19.595 --> 15:20.928
Corcoran: Arrest?

15:20.930 --> 15:24.365
No, we merely invited
the lad to the precinct.

15:24.367 --> 15:27.101
Artsy types love the decor.

15:27.103 --> 15:28.869
- Benjamin, here, was...
- You clowns.

15:28.871 --> 15:31.372
It's bad enough, his father
died a tragic death.

15:31.374 --> 15:33.407
- Now, you're trying to blame him...
- Father is dead?

15:33.409 --> 15:35.509
And now you're trying to
blame him with the murder?

15:35.511 --> 15:37.077
What happened to my father?

15:37.079 --> 15:38.746
Where is he?
What do mean, dead?!

15:38.748 --> 15:40.914
Come on.
Come on!

15:40.916 --> 15:44.017
- What are you talking about?
- Animals!

15:44.019 --> 15:45.753
You couldn't be bothered
to dance a step or two

15:45.755 --> 15:47.254
with him until we'd finished?

15:47.256 --> 15:50.557
I tried, obviously, but
these rich assholes...!

15:50.559 --> 15:51.625
Captain.

15:51.627 --> 15:53.127
Donovan tells me

15:53.129 --> 15:55.863
you specifically promised
him discretion.

15:55.865 --> 16:00.267
Leave piano boy be, for now.

16:00.269 --> 16:01.769
I'll get someone else,
who knows how

16:01.771 --> 16:03.871
to control himself,
to follow him,

16:03.873 --> 16:06.874
make sure he doesn't
run off to Paris!

16:06.876 --> 16:08.575
In the meantime, you two,

16:08.577 --> 16:10.344
solve the damn case!

16:12.380 --> 16:14.381
What I wouldn't give
to tear apart

16:14.383 --> 16:16.250
that pretentious shit's house.

16:16.252 --> 16:18.051
We should work
through this first.

16:18.053 --> 16:19.686
Go by Centre Street,
see if Teresa showed up.

16:19.688 --> 16:20.687
Captain,

16:20.689 --> 16:23.157
could I have a word?

16:28.363 --> 16:31.498
Oh!

16:31.500 --> 16:35.235
Following up on
the Keating witnesses,

16:35.237 --> 16:38.305
have you had any sign of
Annie Reilly, at all?

16:38.307 --> 16:42.810
She's the devil's
brat, Corcoran.

16:42.812 --> 16:44.945
And, in Five Points,

16:44.947 --> 16:47.381
that means
she's half-ghost.

16:47.383 --> 16:48.916
We'll arrest her, one day.

16:48.918 --> 16:51.118
That's just the way it is.

16:51.120 --> 16:53.296
Until then,

16:54.220 --> 16:56.263
don't pretend she's important.

16:57.493 --> 16:58.992
Now, go on, get out of.

17:05.400 --> 17:09.803
And so I am simply a citizen of

17:09.805 --> 17:12.071
the Confederate States
of America.

17:12.074 --> 17:14.368
You have no evidence tying me

17:14.489 --> 17:16.742
to the so-called burnin'
of New York.

17:16.744 --> 17:18.145
Now, I challenge

17:18.146 --> 17:19.813
anyone involved
with these proceedings

17:19.815 --> 17:22.683
to stand and state otherwise!

17:26.387 --> 17:27.820
You have no case,

17:27.823 --> 17:29.923
no evidence.

17:29.925 --> 17:33.494
I'm nothing
but an innocent man.

17:33.496 --> 17:36.897
Thank you.

17:36.899 --> 17:38.932
You may resume your station

17:38.934 --> 17:40.400
at the defense table.

17:48.142 --> 17:50.377
[ Squeaking ]

17:53.982 --> 17:55.415
Hey!

17:55.417 --> 17:56.750
[ Squeak-squeak ]

17:56.752 --> 17:58.185
Piano wire.

17:58.187 --> 17:59.953
Where'd you kids

17:59.955 --> 18:02.456
come across this?

18:02.458 --> 18:04.992
You heard 'im!

18:04.994 --> 18:07.594
Where did you get your toy?

18:07.596 --> 18:08.762
Unh!

18:08.764 --> 18:10.264
It wasn't nobody's!
I found it

18:10.266 --> 18:12.032
in the empty apartment
up top there.

18:12.034 --> 18:15.602
[ Fireworks burst ]

18:15.604 --> 18:17.137
It's all right.

18:17.139 --> 18:19.806
Up there?

18:19.808 --> 18:21.241
Teresa's apartment,

18:21.243 --> 18:22.876
and Benny plays the piano.

18:26.981 --> 18:29.249
Maguire: There's no sign that
Benny boy has been here.

18:29.251 --> 18:31.818
You find anything?

18:31.820 --> 18:33.787
Just this letter.

18:38.726 --> 18:41.228
It's dated two months ago,

18:41.230 --> 18:42.729
from Teresa's mother.

18:43.377 --> 18:44.457
"Dearest daughter,

18:44.577 --> 18:46.567
your father and I
worry so about you.

18:46.569 --> 18:48.965
He is convinced
the city of New York

18:49.085 --> 18:50.327
is devoid of God,

18:50.447 --> 18:51.805
full of repulsive immigrants,

18:51.807 --> 18:55.075
papists, and other cretins.

18:55.077 --> 18:56.610
Things are hard here,
but I have managed

18:56.612 --> 18:59.479
to put aside these
$5 to help you.

18:59.481 --> 19:03.050
It pains us not to have
word. Please write."

19:03.052 --> 19:05.953
The protestant orange bastards.

19:05.955 --> 19:07.387
Don't mind if I do.

19:07.389 --> 19:10.260
No.
Not on my case.

19:11.960 --> 19:13.427
<i>Our</i> case.

19:19.334 --> 19:20.400
Aah!

19:20.402 --> 19:21.802
[ Laughter ]

19:21.804 --> 19:23.937
Bigger noise and
narrower streets are

19:23.939 --> 19:28.709
the least-jarring parts
of Five Points.

19:28.711 --> 19:31.545
Smaller sky stunned us most.

19:31.547 --> 19:33.146
Some nights, you won't be able

19:33.148 --> 19:34.648
to locate the north star.

19:34.650 --> 19:36.783
But you don't need it anymore.

19:36.785 --> 19:40.821
Move in any direction,
you're still free.

19:40.823 --> 19:45.092
Mama, our home.

19:45.094 --> 19:46.159
Which room?

19:46.161 --> 19:50.197
All of them...
Roof to foundation.

19:50.199 --> 19:54.334
You're teasin'.

19:54.336 --> 19:58.305
We earn money and we pay
for the place we choose,

19:58.307 --> 20:00.273
same as the white man
that drove us.

20:07.115 --> 20:08.815
Sybil!

20:08.817 --> 20:10.384
- Get out!
- Honey, there are laws.

20:10.386 --> 20:11.518
There are laws
and I took an oath!

20:11.520 --> 20:13.520
Laws?! Laws?!
Well, here's my law...

20:13.522 --> 20:15.555
Find someplace else to sleep,

20:15.557 --> 20:17.491
and don't be lookin'
for your breakfast here.

20:17.493 --> 20:18.558
[ Laughter ]

20:23.364 --> 20:25.465
Straight up and a room.

20:25.467 --> 20:27.467
Not a chance.

20:27.469 --> 20:29.202
Ugh.

20:29.204 --> 20:31.505
You'll spot me, won't ya?!

20:31.507 --> 20:32.839
Ugh!

20:35.810 --> 20:38.478
This look like
a bank to you, huh?

20:38.480 --> 20:39.479
Eva.

20:39.481 --> 20:41.748
Sounds like Sybil is driving

20:41.750 --> 20:43.383
the O'Brien wagon again, huh?

20:43.385 --> 20:46.019
Oh, Christ.
Here it is...

20:46.021 --> 20:47.888
I was kicked out

20:47.890 --> 20:49.923
when I was already outside.

20:49.925 --> 20:51.958
I got what you see
and that's the sum.

20:53.494 --> 20:55.529
Well,

20:55.531 --> 20:57.264
you help keep order tonight

20:57.266 --> 20:59.666
and you'll get a room.

20:59.668 --> 21:02.536
If copperheads show up
to cause trouble,

21:02.538 --> 21:03.970
you'll convince them otherwise

21:03.972 --> 21:05.338
or escort them out.

21:05.340 --> 21:07.374
You'll sleep in a free bed

21:07.376 --> 21:10.844
when everyone else is
in theirs, paying.

21:10.846 --> 21:12.679
You and my wife

21:12.681 --> 21:15.215
must've been separated
at birth!

21:15.217 --> 21:17.818
You've left me with no case.

21:17.820 --> 21:19.386
I am about to make
a closing statement

21:19.388 --> 21:20.787
and I have no
closing statement.

21:20.789 --> 21:22.155
Recite every detail.

21:22.157 --> 21:23.932
Cataloging all possible
implications

21:24.052 --> 21:24.891
will reveal Kennedy's guilt!

21:24.893 --> 21:26.626
You misunderstand
the mechanics of law.

21:26.628 --> 21:28.895
Please trust me,
I want nothing more

21:28.897 --> 21:30.330
than to proclaim
Kennedy guilty.

21:30.332 --> 21:31.698
Before my statement
disintegrates

21:31.700 --> 21:33.200
into an embarrassment,
I am begging you

21:33.202 --> 21:34.968
to satisfy that desire.

21:34.970 --> 21:36.603
At any moment
before I conclude,

21:36.605 --> 21:39.306
we may add a witness.
Signal to the clerk.

21:39.308 --> 21:41.908
Your testimony may be brief,

21:41.910 --> 21:43.543
but it must happen.

21:56.557 --> 21:58.558
As you can see,

21:58.560 --> 22:01.428
the defendant,
one Robert Cobb Kennedy,

22:01.430 --> 22:03.697
is a Southern sympathizer,

22:03.699 --> 22:06.266
as evidenced by his alliances

22:06.268 --> 22:08.301
and his history as a combatant.

22:08.303 --> 22:12.072
Rail and hotel records
show that,

22:12.074 --> 22:14.007
not only was Kennedy
in New York City

22:14.009 --> 22:15.475
on the day of the arson

22:15.477 --> 22:18.178
at Barnum's Museum
and the six hotels,

22:18.180 --> 22:21.414
he was also registered
at Lovejoy's,

22:21.416 --> 22:22.582
one of the burned.

22:25.214 --> 22:26.424
While there are

22:26.544 --> 22:30.624
no, uh, witnesses available...

22:30.626 --> 22:31.958
while...

22:31.960 --> 22:33.426
while we have, uh...

22:33.428 --> 22:34.761
while,

22:34.763 --> 22:35.962
uh...

22:37.298 --> 22:39.699
Despite registering
at Lovejoy's,

22:39.701 --> 22:41.134
the defendant

22:41.136 --> 22:44.171
disappeared after the fire.

22:44.173 --> 22:45.705
There is no explanation

22:45.707 --> 22:47.974
for this abrupt departure.

22:47.976 --> 22:49.743
Of course,

22:49.745 --> 22:52.045
other individuals
were involved,

22:52.047 --> 22:55.882
however, it is clear
that the, uh...

22:55.884 --> 22:57.276
[ Laughing ]

22:57.396 --> 22:59.352
it is clear that the, uh...

23:11.954 --> 23:15.238
I would like to announce
a new witness.

23:15.358 --> 23:18.572
I call Mr. Morehouse
to the stand.

23:27.882 --> 23:30.750
Mr. <i>Norbert</i>
Morehouse.

23:30.752 --> 23:32.786
[ Spectators murmur ]

23:52.606 --> 23:54.240
Benny needs to explain
why his dad

23:54.242 --> 23:59.345
was killed with piano wire.

23:59.347 --> 24:00.680
Knock again.

24:03.684 --> 24:06.486
We can't even get the Butler.

24:06.488 --> 24:07.920
Here, I got this.

24:07.922 --> 24:09.856
Wait!

24:14.361 --> 24:16.763
[ Thump ]

24:16.765 --> 24:19.432
Something's not right.

24:19.434 --> 24:20.681
Our Benny boy's in there.

24:20.801 --> 24:22.075
I know he is.

24:22.195 --> 24:23.970
Let's not spook him

24:23.972 --> 24:25.571
'til we get him
cuffed, and then...

24:36.717 --> 24:39.919
Oh! Tried to drink
your guilt away,

24:39.921 --> 24:41.421
there, Benny boy?

24:44.541 --> 24:46.228
♪

24:51.331 --> 24:52.598
♪

24:52.600 --> 24:55.668
Ah, tare an'ouns.

24:55.670 --> 24:58.225
What's this, a suicide note?

24:58.345 --> 25:00.105
♪

25:01.402 --> 25:04.277
"When you shall these
unlucky deeds relate,

25:04.279 --> 25:08.147
speak of me as I am;
Nothing extenuate,

25:08.149 --> 25:11.751
nor set down aught in malice:

25:11.753 --> 25:13.252
Then must you speak of one

25:13.254 --> 25:15.488
that loved not wisely,
but too well."

25:15.490 --> 25:17.824
What the hell does that mean?

25:17.826 --> 25:19.926
After threatening me

25:19.928 --> 25:21.694
during our meeting
at Lovejoy's Hotel,

25:21.696 --> 25:24.964
I had no choice but
to deliver the money,

25:24.966 --> 25:26.399
which he, in turn, delivered

25:26.401 --> 25:29.035
to the doorstep of
the traitors,

25:29.037 --> 25:31.704
Greek fire.

25:31.706 --> 25:35.141
That is the extent of
my involvement

25:35.143 --> 25:38.878
and of my witness.

25:38.880 --> 25:42.315
I can, however, confirm
with absolute certainty

25:42.317 --> 25:44.283
that the arson of New York City

25:44.285 --> 25:45.718
was organized

25:45.720 --> 25:49.655
and primarily executed
by that man,

25:49.657 --> 25:52.325
Robert Cobb Kennedy.

25:52.327 --> 25:53.960
Objection.

25:53.962 --> 25:56.195
Quiet!

25:56.197 --> 25:58.231
Any further questions?

25:58.233 --> 25:59.599
Not at the present time.

25:59.601 --> 26:02.935
Then we will allow
for a brief recess.

26:14.548 --> 26:15.982
Welcome back to New York.

26:15.984 --> 26:17.884
All right, get up.

26:17.886 --> 26:19.385
And thank you.

26:19.387 --> 26:21.454
To a man of contracts,
a deal is a deal.

26:21.456 --> 26:22.588
Let's go.

26:23.724 --> 26:25.324
Kennedy:
Elizabeth.

26:25.326 --> 26:27.827
And you're a fool,
if you thought

26:27.829 --> 26:29.362
I would forgo saving Elizabeth

26:29.364 --> 26:30.730
to stay in Atlanta.

26:30.732 --> 26:34.600
That city is hell
with mint juleps.

26:34.602 --> 26:37.169
Remember those words,
because you won't be

26:37.171 --> 26:40.273
getting anything
beyond our agreement.

26:40.275 --> 26:42.575
Still, it is
immensely satisfying

26:42.577 --> 26:44.477
 to hear you admit your mistake

26:44.479 --> 26:46.112
in supporting Kennedy.

26:46.114 --> 26:47.613
The only mistake I made

26:47.615 --> 26:48.681
was getting caught.

26:48.683 --> 26:49.882
Gentlemen.
Excuse me?

26:49.884 --> 26:51.384
Might I suggest that we embrace

26:51.386 --> 26:54.921
this opportunity
for a fresh start,

26:54.923 --> 26:56.923
a new beginning for us all?

26:56.925 --> 26:58.925
Absolutely.

26:58.927 --> 27:01.227
I'd like to see
the two of you behave

27:01.229 --> 27:03.696
like father and son,
just this once.

27:03.698 --> 27:05.998
In memory of your mother.

27:18.178 --> 27:20.151
[ Laughing ]

27:20.271 --> 27:21.677
Needs sugar.

27:22.717 --> 27:25.448
Sugar, in your corn dodger?

27:25.568 --> 27:27.761
You <i>have</i> become a yankee.

27:27.881 --> 27:30.256
If your collards are
as salty as I remember,

27:30.258 --> 27:31.924
we will be clinging to this

27:31.926 --> 27:33.426
sweet yankee cornbread
for dear life.

27:33.428 --> 27:38.197
[ Laughter ]

27:38.199 --> 27:41.033
Mama, here, in the north,

27:41.035 --> 27:43.726
I have become the
woman I want to be.

27:43.846 --> 27:46.814
That's as clear as well water.

27:47.445 --> 27:49.909
I'm proud to be your mother.

27:53.314 --> 27:55.381
Mama, you were almost
a grandmother.

27:59.019 --> 28:02.288
Two months ago, I lost a child.

28:02.290 --> 28:05.224
I know my loss is common,

28:05.226 --> 28:07.593
but with you here,
I want so badly

28:07.595 --> 28:10.663
for my womb
to be able to carry.

28:10.665 --> 28:13.633
I lost four babies
before their births,

28:13.635 --> 28:16.836
two before Louis
came out alive.

28:16.838 --> 28:18.871
Many of us begin motherhood

28:18.873 --> 28:22.842
with miscarriage.

28:22.844 --> 28:26.245
Pregnancy is a feat, darlin'.

28:26.247 --> 28:28.618
Children are
a blessing, but also,

28:28.738 --> 28:30.934
a part of you
that's gone forever.

28:33.821 --> 28:36.155
The things I never
dreamed would happen

28:36.157 --> 28:41.894
between my first baby
and today.

28:41.896 --> 28:43.362
There's all sorts of unexpected

28:43.364 --> 28:44.797
ahead of you.

28:50.109 --> 28:52.905
I'm going to see
if this oven's hot.

28:57.344 --> 29:00.713
<i>"I took by the throat</i>
<i>the circumcised dog</i>

29:00.715 --> 29:02.348
<i>and smote him thus."</i>

29:02.350 --> 29:06.118
<i>Signed, Benjamin Bartlett.</i>

29:06.120 --> 29:08.020
Sounds more like Shakespeare.

29:08.022 --> 29:10.956
Othello's suicide
speech, in fact.

29:10.958 --> 29:15.594
A fella named hello
gives a goodbye speech?

29:15.596 --> 29:19.065
You may finally be getting
a sense of humor.

29:19.067 --> 29:20.633
A good detective or a captain

29:20.635 --> 29:22.234
educates himself
in all culture,

29:22.236 --> 29:26.272
so he may be fluent
in any crime.

29:26.274 --> 29:28.074
Edwin Booth is scheduled
to play the title role

29:28.076 --> 29:30.409
in "Oth-hello"
at the Winter Garden

29:30.411 --> 29:31.911
next month.
I'll get you a ticket.

29:31.913 --> 29:34.280
So Benjamin kills himself

29:34.282 --> 29:37.450
and admits to murdering
his father.

29:37.452 --> 29:39.819
We know that because
this Othello

29:39.939 --> 29:40.784
killed his?

29:40.904 --> 29:42.643
No, the moor killed his wife.

29:42.763 --> 29:44.345
He believed her
unfaithful, although

29:44.465 --> 29:48.294
she had just misplaced
a handkerchief.

29:48.296 --> 29:50.996
Benjamin seemed
genuinely surprised

29:50.998 --> 29:52.431
to learn of his father's death.

29:52.433 --> 29:54.100
Don't be naive!

29:54.102 --> 29:56.602
Every guilty man's most
rehearsed expression

29:56.604 --> 29:57.770
is disbelief.

29:57.772 --> 30:00.740
And you do cling to cases like

30:00.742 --> 30:02.675
a swooning debutante
to her folding fan,

30:02.677 --> 30:04.810
and nearly as emotional.

30:04.812 --> 30:06.112
[ Laughter ]

30:08.682 --> 30:10.583
I heard about the scene
at the Bartlett Mansion.

30:10.585 --> 30:12.218
On the spectrum of humanity,

30:12.220 --> 30:13.819
let's move toward urban man

30:13.821 --> 30:16.489
and away from pillaging
viking, shall we?

30:16.491 --> 30:17.990
But what is life,

30:17.992 --> 30:20.826
if we do not have improvements

30:20.828 --> 30:22.862
to which to aspire to?

30:22.864 --> 30:26.432
To approaching Grace.

30:26.434 --> 30:27.800
<i>Slainte.</i>

30:41.281 --> 30:44.884
Spring certainly has
inspired Five Points.

30:44.886 --> 30:47.153
I carry another child?

30:47.155 --> 30:50.055
Yes.

30:50.057 --> 30:53.092
Kevin has left our home.

30:53.094 --> 30:55.394
I heard such, but that
doesn't mean...

30:55.396 --> 30:56.896
Has he taken up
at the whorehouse?

30:56.898 --> 30:58.764
Ellen,

30:58.766 --> 31:02.568
it is not my position
to sort this out.

31:02.570 --> 31:05.171
I think you know
what you need to do.

31:05.173 --> 31:06.672
Go find him.

31:06.674 --> 31:08.374
Find a way to talk to him.

31:16.950 --> 31:18.717
I would very much
like to commend

31:18.719 --> 31:20.820
the detectives
of the 6th precinct

31:20.822 --> 31:22.321
for their commitment to order,

31:22.323 --> 31:24.056
especially on this,

31:24.058 --> 31:27.293
a National Day of Celebration.

31:27.295 --> 31:29.628
From tragic suicide and murder,

31:29.630 --> 31:32.464
we move forward to a better

31:32.466 --> 31:34.333
and more ordered community.

31:34.335 --> 31:35.768
Of course,
our thoughts and prayers

31:35.770 --> 31:38.737
are with the Bartlett
family and friends.

31:38.739 --> 31:39.939
Anything else, gentlemen?

31:39.941 --> 31:42.007
Do you have any motive
why Benjamin Bartlett...?

31:42.009 --> 31:46.212
Feels good to close
a case with you again.

31:46.214 --> 31:48.914
We solved the case
from some poetry?

31:48.916 --> 31:50.716
Makes the bosses happy.

31:50.718 --> 31:52.885
What about the stuff
you can touch,

31:52.887 --> 31:53.986
the evidence?

31:53.988 --> 31:55.354
You know what touches me?

31:55.356 --> 31:57.356
A stiff drink.
Eva's got me

31:57.358 --> 32:00.359
roughing copperheads
for a room tonight.

32:00.361 --> 32:02.027
Come round, save me from some

32:02.029 --> 32:03.529
inauguration idiots, will ya?

32:03.531 --> 32:04.897
There's a wife and a mistress

32:04.899 --> 32:05.998
unaccounted for,

32:06.000 --> 32:08.033
a mansion with no staff
of any kind,

32:08.035 --> 32:09.735
and a murderer who
supposedly destroys

32:09.737 --> 32:11.237
his most prized possession

32:11.239 --> 32:12.972
to build his murder weapon.

32:12.974 --> 32:14.974
This case isn't done.

32:14.976 --> 32:16.976
I asked Sullivan about Annie.

32:16.978 --> 32:18.577
He didn't lie.

32:18.579 --> 32:21.647
Kevin, some things,
this city just swallows.

32:21.649 --> 32:23.281
Come to Eva's.

32:32.404 --> 32:34.405
[ Knock at door ]

32:41.210 --> 32:42.421
Ellen: Francis?

32:53.759 --> 32:56.394
Ellen, why are you here?

32:58.063 --> 33:00.031
"The said Kennedy shall be hung

33:00.033 --> 33:02.467
by the neck until he be dead,

33:02.469 --> 33:03.968
at such time and place

33:03.970 --> 33:06.137
as the Commanding
General may direct."

33:06.139 --> 33:09.107
Per our agreement,

33:09.109 --> 33:11.476
I did not testify against you.

33:11.478 --> 33:14.212
As you claim to be
a man of honor,

33:14.214 --> 33:16.147
I entrust that you will keep

33:16.149 --> 33:17.282
your end of the bargain.

33:17.284 --> 33:19.918
Knowledge of
Elizabeth's involvement

33:19.920 --> 33:21.419
will end with your death.

33:21.421 --> 33:26.591
[ Laughs ]

33:26.593 --> 33:30.061
Oh, Robert,

33:30.063 --> 33:33.431
your cleverness
has always lacked

33:33.433 --> 33:37.001
a certain vision, hasn't it?

33:37.003 --> 33:38.503
Such leaps in logic.

33:38.505 --> 33:41.339
How could I possibly
accuse your wife

33:41.341 --> 33:44.442
when I, myself, am innocent?

33:46.220 --> 33:47.904
Do you think your choices

33:48.024 --> 33:49.235
will not haunt you?!

34:01.260 --> 34:05.363
This silence

34:05.365 --> 34:06.864
makes me mad.

34:12.504 --> 34:14.739
This silence...

34:16.809 --> 34:21.813
That isn't silence.

34:21.815 --> 34:23.447
It fills me.

34:28.920 --> 34:32.090
Christ, I've missed you.

35:11.697 --> 35:13.564
I can't, Francis!

35:13.566 --> 35:16.000
I can't.
We can't.

35:16.002 --> 35:18.603
Oh.

35:18.605 --> 35:20.938
We shouldn't make
the same mistakes.

35:20.940 --> 35:22.774
Mistakes?

35:22.776 --> 35:25.109
And  you're here because

35:25.111 --> 35:27.896
you want to say to my face
I'm a mistake?

35:29.149 --> 35:31.382
You thought of me
because I'm a glaring,

35:31.384 --> 35:32.784
overwhelming mistake?

35:32.786 --> 35:36.788
I need life back,
Francis, real life.

35:36.790 --> 35:38.289
Don't treat me

35:38.291 --> 35:39.824
like a fool who
invented a world.

35:39.826 --> 35:41.426
What we had...

35:41.428 --> 35:43.061
I'm talking about a return

35:43.063 --> 35:45.229
to real living,
not sitting at home,

35:45.231 --> 35:46.631
feeling something has
crawled into my heart.

35:46.633 --> 35:49.701
- Ellen...
- I can't take a full breath!

35:49.703 --> 35:51.202
You wonder why you
feel half-alive?

35:51.204 --> 35:52.970
You spend your days
pining after a man

35:52.972 --> 35:54.172
who will never forgive ya,

35:54.174 --> 35:57.742
a man who despises you
to his very core!

35:57.744 --> 35:59.844
You want to play the role
of doting wife?

35:59.846 --> 36:02.080
Go right ahead! But don't
you dare insult me

36:02.082 --> 36:04.148
by acting like
what we had wasn't good,

36:04.150 --> 36:05.717
won't be forever a part of ya.

36:05.719 --> 36:08.152
Don't disrespect
our child like that.

36:08.154 --> 36:13.257
Our child would be
six months old now.

36:13.259 --> 36:14.759
Do you count his birthdays?

36:14.761 --> 36:16.761
Not just the months,
but the mornings?

36:16.763 --> 36:18.196
Do you wake up thinkin'

36:18.198 --> 36:19.697
of his wee hands so fiercely

36:19.699 --> 36:21.866
that you look down,
expecting to be holding

36:21.868 --> 36:25.870
a soft thing,
all love and need?

36:25.872 --> 36:29.173
Eyes of your green,

36:29.175 --> 36:30.675
hair of me brown.

36:40.386 --> 36:44.689
If you had chosen me,

36:44.691 --> 36:47.992
I never woulda left you.

36:51.230 --> 36:55.500
Remember that

36:55.502 --> 36:57.935
in the middle of the night

36:57.937 --> 36:59.604
as you lie in bed alone.

37:01.373 --> 37:03.341
[ Crying ]

37:12.630 --> 37:13.864
<i>Dearest daughter,</i>

37:13.866 --> 37:15.966
<i>your father and I</i>
<i>worry so about you.</i>

37:15.968 --> 37:17.501
<i>He's convinced</i>
<i>the city of New York</i>

37:17.503 --> 37:19.169
<i>is devoid of God...</i>

37:19.171 --> 37:20.771
<i>Things are hard here,</i>
<i>but I've managed</i>

37:20.773 --> 37:23.674
<i>to put aside</i>
<i>these $5 to help you.</i>

37:23.676 --> 37:25.942
<i>It pains us not to have</i>
<i>word. Please write.</i>

37:25.944 --> 37:27.611
<i>Your loving mother.</i>

37:33.718 --> 37:38.522
♪ Behold, the chief
who now commands ♪

37:38.524 --> 37:43.794
♪ once more to serve
his country stands ♪

37:43.796 --> 37:47.831
Donovan!

37:48.207 --> 37:50.465
Corky, I need to talk to you.

37:50.467 --> 37:51.466
Not now.

37:51.468 --> 37:53.902
- Just for a moment.
- I can't.

37:53.904 --> 37:55.503
Hey, Donovan,

37:55.505 --> 37:56.871
about the Bartlett case...

37:56.873 --> 37:58.940
When I was on the force,
I used to love

37:58.942 --> 38:00.241
cases like the Bartletts.

38:00.243 --> 38:03.445
Wrap 'em up,
get down to the pub

38:03.447 --> 38:04.946
for a wee one on the way home.

38:04.948 --> 38:07.515
But something tells me
you are not as pleased.

38:07.517 --> 38:09.557
The solution was too easy.

38:09.677 --> 38:11.434
Sometimes crimes
are just that easy,

38:11.554 --> 38:14.222
turning on base human
nature and nothing more.

38:14.224 --> 38:16.958
Sometimes you have to
learn to accept

38:16.960 --> 38:19.694
the animal inside of us, hmm?

38:19.696 --> 38:22.077
Respect the opportunity

38:22.197 --> 38:24.666
to move on towards
the more evolved.

38:24.668 --> 38:28.737
♪ Rallying around our liberty ♪

38:28.739 --> 38:30.004
[ Spits ]

38:30.006 --> 38:32.240
I'm certain the
alderman's farm girl

38:32.242 --> 38:34.709
knows exactly what
happened in that room,

38:34.711 --> 38:36.211
and, if Teresa Trembley
doesn't know

38:36.213 --> 38:37.712
why it happened,
I can find out.

38:37.714 --> 38:40.315
Okay, now, I understand.
I understand.

38:40.317 --> 38:42.250
You see the full story.

38:42.252 --> 38:44.619
Clean might be comforting,

38:44.621 --> 38:47.288
but you really think,
in solving these cases,

38:47.290 --> 38:48.690
it explains why happenstance

38:48.692 --> 38:50.058
seizes hold of our lives.

38:50.060 --> 38:51.426
You, Kevin Corcoran,

38:51.428 --> 38:52.961
think the full story

38:52.963 --> 38:54.896
helps us solve ourselves

38:54.898 --> 38:56.397
and, while I rarely share

38:56.399 --> 38:58.133
your precise incentive,

38:58.135 --> 39:00.168
I am always fascinated

39:00.170 --> 39:03.104
by your dedication.

39:03.106 --> 39:05.173
Thank you, sir.

39:05.175 --> 39:08.576
♪ With equal skill,
with God-like pow'r ♪

39:08.578 --> 39:12.147
♪ he governs in the fearful ♪

39:12.149 --> 39:15.750
We rarely imbibe, but this

39:15.752 --> 39:17.719
is the rarest of days.

39:23.207 --> 39:24.698
To you,

39:25.328 --> 39:29.564
here, safe.

39:29.566 --> 39:31.065
To this fine home.

39:31.067 --> 39:32.801
And to Lincoln,

39:32.803 --> 39:34.602
for what he has done
and what he will do.

39:40.810 --> 39:42.978
When the president
first took office,

39:42.980 --> 39:46.148
I realized real pride,
national belonging,

39:46.150 --> 39:48.116
could rise in my chest.

39:48.118 --> 39:49.318
I felt connected
to this country,

39:49.320 --> 39:50.752
as to a grand being.

39:50.754 --> 39:52.354
Unfortunately, that grand being

39:52.356 --> 39:55.190
was more comfortable
with you as a slave,

39:55.192 --> 39:56.591
and you still aren't allowed

39:56.593 --> 39:58.026
to elect your fair hero.

39:58.028 --> 40:00.696
Well, Lincoln is
a champion of education,

40:00.698 --> 40:02.431
land for the poor, and,

40:02.433 --> 40:03.965
I believe, in the end,

40:03.967 --> 40:06.034
true emancipation.

40:06.036 --> 40:07.636
We will have the right to vote.

40:07.638 --> 40:09.971
Well, I don't trust
a white man's

40:09.973 --> 40:12.274
good intentions,
until they're gone

40:12.276 --> 40:14.741
so far, he can't undo 'em.

40:16.913 --> 40:18.313
Whoo-hoo-hoo!

40:18.315 --> 40:21.016
Are we certain that
they celebratin'?

40:21.018 --> 40:23.385
With the Irish, sometimes
celebration and riot

40:23.387 --> 40:25.620
are notes of the same song.

40:25.622 --> 40:27.923
[ Telegraph transmits ]

40:27.925 --> 40:29.791
Morehouse: "With high hope
for the future,

40:29.793 --> 40:31.360
no prediction

40:31.362 --> 40:33.028
in regard to it is ventured.

40:33.030 --> 40:35.397
On the occasion
corresponding to this

40:35.399 --> 40:36.832
four years ago,

40:36.834 --> 40:40.102
all thoughts
were anxiously directed

40:40.104 --> 40:42.971
to an impending civil war...

40:42.973 --> 40:44.706
Insurgent agents
were in the city

40:44.708 --> 40:47.175
seeking to destroy it
without war...

40:47.295 --> 40:50.312
Seeking to dissolve
the union...

40:50.314 --> 40:53.115
neither party expected
for the war

40:53.117 --> 40:55.217
the magnitude or the duration

40:55.219 --> 40:59.154
which it has
already attained...

40:59.156 --> 41:01.423
each looked
for an easier triumph,

41:01.425 --> 41:03.158
and a result less fundamental

41:03.160 --> 41:05.227
and less astounding."

41:05.229 --> 41:06.695
And so he says...

41:06.697 --> 41:08.518
"With charity for all,

41:08.638 --> 41:11.533
with firmness
in the right..."

41:11.535 --> 41:13.034
I need to use

41:13.036 --> 41:14.536
your telegraph machine

41:14.538 --> 41:15.971
to Ontario, police business.

41:15.973 --> 41:17.706
Happy inauguration

41:17.708 --> 41:19.241
to you, too, Corky.

41:19.243 --> 41:20.742
The system's been overwhelmed,

41:20.744 --> 41:22.878
but now the address
has come through...

41:22.880 --> 41:25.747
Everyone seems to be
feting our leader...

41:25.749 --> 41:27.249
Have a go.

41:32.488 --> 41:33.922
This will be sent

41:33.924 --> 41:35.424
to the family
of Teresa Trembley.

41:35.426 --> 41:38.160
Where was I?

41:38.162 --> 41:41.596
"Let us strive on to finish
the work we are in,

41:41.598 --> 41:43.999
to bind up the nation's wounds,

41:44.001 --> 41:47.169
to care for him who shall
have borne the battle

41:47.171 --> 41:50.172
and for his widow
and his orphan,

41:50.174 --> 41:52.240
to do all which may
achieve and cherish

41:52.242 --> 41:55.911
a just
and lasting peace."

41:55.913 --> 41:58.814
To peace.

41:58.816 --> 42:00.315
- Peace.
- Peace.

42:02.285 --> 42:03.985
Norbert:
And to Lincoln.

42:03.987 --> 42:05.220
- And to Lincoln.
- To Lincoln.

42:05.222 --> 42:06.855
[ Glasses clink ]

42:07.743 --> 42:09.901
